OL,3,CHow a toddler was targeted by his own
OL,4,Cfamily in the weeks before his murder
OL,6,FJurors in the trial at Mold Crown
OL,7,FCourt saw Ethan's smiling face every
OL,8,Fday. His photograph was in the
OL,9,Fmaterial they were given on day one.
OL,10,FProsecuting Barrister, Caroline Rees
OL,11,FKC, opened the case in June by telling
OL,12,Fthe 12 men and women: "The victim is a
OL,13,Flittle boy called Ethan Ives-
OL,14,FGriffiths".
OL,16,FShe asked them to look at his
OL,17,Fphotograph so they knew who this trial
OL,18,Fwas about. That was their introduction
OL,19,Fto a small two-year-old whose life was
OL,20,Fmarred by ridicule and cruelty.
