OL,3,CHow a toddler was targeted by his own
OL,4,Cfamily in the weeks before his murder
OL,6,FInstead of calling an ambulance or
OL,7,Fdoctor, Ethan was taken to the
OL,8,Fsupermarket.
OL,10,FA medical expert, Dr Sarah Dixon said
OL,11,Fit was "incomprehensible" that
OL,12,Fresponsible adults failed to take
OL,13,FEthan to a GP. It was her belief that
OL,14,Fthe toddler suffered an inflicted
OL,15,Ftraumatic head injury 10 days before
OL,16,Fanother injury inflicted on the 14
OL,17,FAugust.
OL,19,FShe believed he was not taken to be
OL,20,Fseen by health professionals to avoid
OL,21,Fthem suspecting child abuse.
